# --- TEN OF WANDS ---

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands
@if cards[0].reversed:
    The Ten of Wands — reversed. A figure bent under a bundle of ten staves, but upside down, the staves are falling. Letting go, or falling apart. The burden shifting.

    Dev looks at it. "That person is having a bad time."

    "That person is carrying everything themselves. Reversed means something about that is changing. Or needs to."

    Scout, from the vinyl bins, tilts his head. He's looking at the card the way he looks at an album cover — reading the visual composition, the posture, the story in the image. His hand goes to his headphones, a reflex. When Scout encounters something heavy, he reaches for music.

    Behind the counter, Delphi pours herself a fresh cup. Slowly. The way she does when she's about to say something she's been thinking for a while but hasn't. She doesn't say it yet. The tea steeps.

    + ["Reversed, this card is asking what happens if you put some of those staves down. Not all of them — I know you can't put all of them down. But what if the load is supposed to be shared? What if carrying everything alone isn't strength — it's just what you learned because there was nobody else to carry it?"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_R_Empathic
    + ["Ten of Wands reversed often means a burden being released — or needing to be. You've been carrying this alone. Not just the math. The whole thing. Being the first one in your family to do this, with nobody ahead of you on the trail to say 'here's where it gets steep, here's where you need to rest.' That's what this card sees."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_R_Reframing
    + ["This card reversed means you're overburdened. Have you considered dropping a class?"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_R_Blunt
    + ["Reversed Ten of Wands means the pressure is easing. Things should get lighter soon."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_R_Vague
@else:
    The Ten of Wands. A figure bent under a bundle of ten staves, carrying them alone, unable to see the road ahead because the load blocks the view. Burden. Responsibility. The weight of doing everything yourself because you don't know any other way.

    Dev stares at it. His jaw tightens. Something about the image — the solitary figure, the impossible load, the road ahead invisible under the weight — hits a frequency he recognizes.

    Scout sees it land. He takes a step back from the vinyl bins, giving the moment room, the way a sound engineer pulls a fader back to let a vocal breathe. His hand rests on a record spine — not fidgeting, anchoring.

    Mal's pen stops. They're watching Dev's hands. The fists. Mal knows hands — they catalog people the way they catalog books, by what the body says when the mouth is being careful.

    Delphi doesn't move. But the quality of her stillness deepens. She's reading Dev reading the card, the same way she read Ellen reading The Empress. Looking for the crack where the light gets in.

    + ["This card is about carrying everything alone. Not because you're a martyr — because you literally don't know another way. You've been the person your family counts on since you were old enough to be counted on. The smart one. The one who's going to make it. And now you're in a class where 'making it' requires a kind of thinking nobody taught you, and you can't tell your parents because they'd worry, and you can't tell your professors because they seem like they were born knowing this, and you can't tell your friends because—"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_U_Empathic
    + ["Ten wands. Count them — ten separate obligations this person is carrying, and not one of them is optional, and not one of them is somebody else's. That's not a workload. That's an identity. You *are* the person who carries things. The question this card asks is: who carries *you?*"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_U_Poetic
    + ["This card represents being overburdened. You're taking on too much. Maybe the double major is too ambitious right now."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_U_Practical
    + ["Heavy card. You're carrying a lot right now."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_U_Vague
@endif

# Ten of Wands — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_U_Empathic
"This card is about carrying everything alone. Not because you're a martyr — because you literally don't know another way."

Dev's breathing changes. Shorter. You're close to something.

"You've been the person your family counts on since you were old enough to be counted on. The smart one. The one who's going to make it. And now you're in a class where 'making it' requires a kind of thinking nobody taught you—"

"Nobody taught me *anything,*" Dev says. Fast. Involuntary. Like it escaped. "I mean — my parents taught me everything. Work ethic, discipline, how to show up. But the academic stuff — the how-to-study, the how-to-ask-for-help, the 'go to office hours, go to the tutoring center, ask a classmate' — I didn't have that. My mom didn't go to college. My dad didn't go to college. My grandparents—" He stops. His voice has gone rough. "I figured everything out myself. Since third grade. And it *worked.* Until it didn't."

The store is very quiet. Outside, the rain intensifies — the heavy Oregon rain that makes the windows run like they're crying on your behalf so you don't have to.

From the vinyl bins, Scout exhales. Quiet. The sound he makes when a lyric lands and he needs a second.

Mal writes something in the composition notebook. One word. You can't see it, but you can hear the single deliberate pen-stroke: one word, underlined.

