# Ten of Wands — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_TenWands_R_Empathic
"Reversed, this card is asking what happens if you put some of those staves down."

Dev: "I can't—"

"Not all of them. I know you can't put all of them down. But what if the load is supposed to be shared?"

His hands unclench. Slightly.

"What if carrying everything alone isn't strength — it's just what you learned because there was nobody else to carry it?"

The word *learned* does something. Dev is a smart kid — the kind of smart that hears a reframing and can't unhear it. The carrying-as-learned-behavior instead of carrying-as-virtue. A program he's been running since third grade, when he realized that his parents couldn't help with the math homework and his teacher couldn't explain it in a way that made sense and so he just... figured it out. Alone. At the kitchen table at Mehta's Kitchen, between the dinner rush and closing, with the sound of his dad's voice calling orders in Marathi and the sizzle of the tandoor and his mom wiping down tables and Dev with a textbook he'd checked out from the library because they couldn't afford to buy it.

"I'm good at carrying things," he says. Quiet. "I don't know how to not."

"That's what this card sees."

