"This card is about systems of order. You've been operating inside a system your whole life — the system of 'work hard, be smart, figure it out.' And it's a good system. It got you through calc 1, 2, 3. It got you into Carruth."

Dev nods. Carefully.

"But real analysis isn't inside that system. It requires a different kind of thinking — abstract, proof-based, structural. And nobody told you the rules changed."

"Nobody told me because nobody in my life *knows* the rules changed." He says this without bitterness. Just precision. The matter-of-fact clarity of a kid who realized early that the world gives some people maps and other people compasses and some people neither, and you navigate with what you've got.

"My high school math teacher was great. Mrs. Patterson. She taught calc and she loved it. But she'd never taken a proof-based course either. She couldn't have warned me about this if she'd wanted to."

