"Reversed Emperor can mean issues with a father figure or authority. Is your relationship with your parents putting pressure on your academics?"

Dev's face goes flat. Not angry — protected. The specific expression of a first-generation kid who has just been asked to pathologize the people who work sixteen-hour days so he can sit in a reading nook and talk about tarot cards.

"My parents are great."

"Of course, I didn't mean—"

"My parents are *great.*"

The door that opened is now reinforced with steel. Behind the counter, Delphi's eyes close briefly. The reading just stepped on a landmine.

