# --- KNIGHT OF PENTACLES ---

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPentacles
@if cards[0].reversed:
    The Knight of Pentacles — reversed. A mounted figure, patient and methodical, on a slow horse — but inverted. The diligence has become stagnation. The patience has curdled into stubbornness. The person who does everything right and still isn't moving.

    Dev looks at it and his breath catches. You wonder if he's seeing the horse or the rider — the animal doing exactly what it's told, going exactly where it's pointed, and getting nowhere.

    Scout is leaning against the bin divider labeled "Slow Burns & Late Bloomers" — his section of albums that take three listens before they click. He's watching Dev with the particular attention of someone who recognizes a fellow late bloomer. Scout didn't know music was his *thing* until he was nineteen and heard Sufjan Stevens' *Illinois* on a road trip to Bend and had to pull over because he was crying too hard to drive.

    Delphi's mug is on the counter. Not in her hand — on the counter. Untouched. That means this one matters.

    + ["Reversed, this knight has been doing everything right — showing up, working hard, following the path — and it's not working anymore. Not because the effort is wrong. Because the effort is pointed at the wrong thing. You're the most disciplined person in that classroom and you're failing, and that contradiction is eating you alive because *discipline has always been enough.*"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_R_Empathic
    + ["This reversal means the approach itself has stalled. You've been applying computational thinking to a proof-based problem — like using a hammer on a screw. The hammer isn't broken. The screw isn't broken. The combination is broken."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_R_Reframing
    + ["Reversed Knight of Pentacles means you're stuck in a rut. Maybe try a different study approach."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_R_Blunt
    + ["This reversed card suggests stagnation. Things aren't moving forward."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_R_Vague
@else:
    The Knight of Pentacles. A mounted figure on a heavy horse, moving slowly but deliberately through a landscape. No urgency. No flash. Just steady, methodical progress toward something that matters. The most patient knight in the deck. The one who always shows up.

    Dev studies the card with the recognition of someone seeing themselves in a mirror they didn't know was there.

    "That's... a very slow horse."

    "It's the knight who does the work. Not the flashy one, not the passionate one, not the clever one. The one who shows up every day and puts one foot in front of the other."

    Scout, from behind the vinyl bins: "That's the Springsteen knight. *Born to Run* is the Knight of Wands. This guy is *Nebraska.* Same artist, completely different gear."

    Mal looks up from the composition notebook. Gives Scout a look. The look means: *that was actually good.*

    Delphi just watches. She already knows where this card goes. She's been watching Dev since he walked in and she saw the Knight of Pentacles walking through the rain with a backpack full of bricks, doing what he always does: showing up.

    + ["This is you. Not the struggle — the *person.* The one who does their own taxes at sixteen. The one who figured out long division alone because nobody could show them. The one who walks into a store they've never been in, in the rain, looking for a textbook, because Thursday is coming and they don't quit. The card isn't showing me your burden. It's showing me your *engine.*"] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_U_Empathic
    + ["The Knight of Pentacles is the most underestimated card in the deck. No drama, no miracles — just relentless, patient, unglamorous work. But here's the thing about this knight: he always arrives. He's slow, but he *always* arrives. The question isn't whether you'll make it through analysis. The question is whether you'll let anyone help you get there faster."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_U_Poetic
    + ["This card represents hard work and dedication. You're clearly putting in the effort."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_U_Practical
    + ["A diligent card. Shows you're a hard worker."] -> TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_U_Vague
@endif

# Knight of Pentacles — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_U_Empathic
"This is you. Not the struggle — the *person.*"

Dev watches you.

"The one who does their own taxes at sixteen. The one who figured out long division alone because nobody could show them."

His eyes widen slightly. You didn't know that. You couldn't have known that. But the cards know, or the store knows, or you know because the reading knows what it needs to know.

"The one who walks into a store they've never been in, in the rain, looking for a textbook, because Thursday is coming and they don't quit."

Dev's throat moves. He swallows hard.

"The card isn't showing me your burden. It's showing me your *engine.* And your engine is incredible. But even the best engine stalls if the fuel is wrong."

From behind the counter, Delphi picks up her mug. Takes a sip. Sets it down. *That one landed.*

Dev's fists unclench. For the first time since he walked in, his hands are open. Palms on the table. The posture of someone who just stopped fighting, not because they gave up, but because someone finally said the thing that made fighting unnecessary.

"My dadi says something like that." His voice is rough. "In Marathi. *Ghoda changla ahe, rasta chukla.* The horse is good. The road is wrong."

