# Knight of Pentacles — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P1_KnightPent_R_Empathic
"Reversed, this knight has been doing everything right — showing up, working hard, following the path — and it's not working anymore."

Dev's jaw clenches.

"Not because the effort is wrong. Because the effort is pointed at the wrong thing. You're the most disciplined person in that classroom and you're *failing*, and that contradiction is eating you alive because discipline has always been enough."

"Always." Dev's voice is hoarse. "Every class. Every test. Every problem set. I just worked harder than everyone else. More hours. More practice problems. Brute force." He almost laughs. "That's literally what we call it in CS. Brute force. Try every possibility until one works."

"And real analysis?"

"Real analysis doesn't *have* every possibility. You have to—" He stops. "You have to see the structure. And I can't. I keep staring at the proofs and they're like... like reading a novel in a language where I know every word but not the grammar."

Mal makes a sound. Small. Involuntary. The sound of someone who just heard their own experience described by a stranger.

