# Eight of Swords — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P2_EightSwords_R_Empathic
"Reversed, the blindfold is slipping. You're starting to see that the thing trapping you isn't real analysis — it's the story you're telling yourself *about* real analysis."

Dev is listening. Really listening, for maybe the first time since he sat down.

"'I'm not smart enough.' 'Everyone else gets it.' 'I'm the only one struggling.'"

"I *am* the only one struggling. Nobody else in the class—"

"Nobody else in the class is telling you they're struggling. That's different."

Dev goes quiet. You can see the reframe happening in real time — the CS major's brain running the new input through existing models and finding that it changes the output.

"My lab partner," he says slowly. "Priya. She always has the problem sets done. Always. But last week she was in the library at 1am and she looked—" He stops. "She looked like me."

"The swords aren't touching you, Dev. They're not touching Priya either. You're all standing in the same circle, blindfolded, thinking you're alone."

