:: TheKind.Session2.P2_TwoSwords_U_Reframing
"There's a concept in CS called a deadlock — two processes each waiting for the other to release a resource."

Dev's eyes sharpen. You're speaking his language.

"That's this card. Part of you knows you need a different approach. Part of you is afraid that admitting that means everything before was wrong. Neither part will yield. So you're frozen."

"A deadlock." He turns the word over. "The solution to a deadlock is to break the symmetry. Force one process to yield."

"Which one yields?"

He thinks. The CS major thinking, but also the kid from Mehta's Kitchen thinking, the kid who's never had anyone to debug this with.

"The 'I can do this alone' part," he says quietly. "That one yields."

Mal, from the edge of the aisle, barely audible: "Good."

