# Two of Swords — Reversed interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P2_TwoSwords_R_Empathic
"Reversed, the swords are dropping. The thing you've been refusing to confront — the fact that you need *help*, real help, structural help — is becoming impossible to avoid."

Dev's breath goes shallow.

"You walked into this store looking for a textbook. You know that's not what you need. You've known for weeks."

"I thought if I just read it enough times—"

"You read Rudin enough times, you memorize Rudin. You still don't learn to prove. It's the wrong tool, Dev. You're not stupid. You brought a wrench to a job that needs a key."

Dev sets down the mug. His hands are shaking slightly. Not from cold.

"Nobody in my family has ever asked for academic help. Because nobody in my family has ever *been* in a position to ask. My dad taught himself restaurant management from a library book. My mom taught herself English from *Sesame Street* and the customers. We don't ask. We figure it out."

He looks at the card. At the swords, falling.

"But this is the first time figuring it out isn't working."

"Because this is the first time it's not about effort. It's about having the right starting point."

