# Ace of Wands — Upright interpretations

:: TheKind.Session2.P3_AceWands_U_Empathic
"The Ace of Wands is the spark. The moment before understanding — not understanding itself, but the moment your brain goes 'wait, I think I see it.'"

Dev nods. He knows this moment. Every coder knows this moment.

"You've had it before. Every time you solved a coding problem that seemed impossible. Every time the algorithm clicked."

"The neural net," Dev says. "Last semester. I spent two weeks getting garbage outputs and then at 3am I found a dimension mismatch in the tensor reshape and suddenly it *worked* and I—" He almost laughs. "I woke up my roommate yelling."

"That spark is your strength, Dev. It's not gone. It's just waiting for the right fuel."

"The right fuel." He looks at the card. At the green, living wand. "Not Rudin."

"Not Rudin."

